# stack. Each subsystem exposes tiny read-only getters (it owns its own
# parallel-array globals; procfs can't reach them directly).
#   socket.ad : kernel socket table (UDP/TCP slot tuples + state)
#   tcp.ad    : TCB table (TCP state machine, per-slot ports/remote IP)
#   arp.ad    : ARP cache entries
